other_tests.findings: 400 erythrocytes per cubic millimeter and no leukocytes. Staining for the presence of bacteria, mycobacteria, and fungi was negative.
Pleural fluid that was turbid and yellow; laboratory tests showed elevated levels of glucose, total protein, lactate dehydrogenase, and a white-cell count with 79 percent polymorphonuclear cells.
other_tests.changes_over_time: A repeated chest radiograph showed decreased size of the pneumothorax, with nearly full expansion of the left lung.

other_tests.findings: Right-sided facial droop and flaccid paralysis of the right arm and leg with brisk reflexes on the right side.
other_tests.changes_over_time: After treatment, the facial droop was gone, and the patient was able to stand unassisted.
